<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,448]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,310,306,332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Remark:</emphasis>
This species was first described on 
<taxonomicName box="[748,880,306,331]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Gossypium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[748,880,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Gossypium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. from 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1059,306,332]" name="Togo" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Togo</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zacher" box="[1075,1238,306,332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" refString="Zacher, F. (1921) Neue und wenig bekannte Spinnmilben. Zeitschrift fur Angewandte Entomologie, 7, 181 - 187." type="journal article" year="1921">
Zacher, 
<number box="[1174,1238,306,332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" value="1921.0">1921</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This species is widely distributed in the Afrotropics and Neotropics and it has a wide host range. In Africa, it is considered as a pest of cassava. An earlier record of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[769,846,384,410]" name="Kenya" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Kenya</collectingCountry>
was by Nyiira (
<number box="[1032,1093,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" value="1982.0">1982</number>
) on an unspecified host plant and location.
</paragraph>
